# {{ project_name }}

Built with [genai-tk](https://github.com/tclatos/genai-tk).

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install dependencies
uv sync

# Try the example CLI commands
uv run cli example joke "Python"
uv run cli example chain "AI engineers"
uv run cli example agent "What is the capital of France?"

# Launch the web interface
make webapp
```

## Project Structure

```
{{ package_name }}/
├── main/
│   └── streamlit.py           # Streamlit webapp entry point
├── commands/
│   └── example_commands.py    # Example CLI commands (joke, chain, agent, deerflow)
├── chains/
│   └── joke_chain.py          # Example LCEL chain
└── webapp/pages/demos/
    └── hello_agent.py         # Example Streamlit agent page
config/
├── app_conf.yaml              # Main configuration
├── baseline.yaml              # LLM and embeddings defaults
├── webapp.yaml                # Web UI settings
├── agents/                    # Agent profile configs
└── providers/                 # LLM provider configs
```

## Adding New Features

### New CLI Command

1. Create a command class extending `CliTopCommand` in `{{ package_name }}/commands/`
2. Register it in `config/app_conf.yaml` under `cli.commands`

### New Webapp Page

1. Create a Streamlit page in `{{ package_name }}/webapp/pages/demos/`
2. Register it in `config/webapp.yaml` under `ui.navigation`

### New Agent Profile

Edit `config/agents/langchain.yaml` to add profiles with tools and MCP servers.

See the [genai-tk documentation](https://github.com/tclatos/genai-tk) for details.
